                     <interp inst="t17160712-3-off15" type="offenceSubcategory" value="seditiousLibel"></interp>
               indicted for a, Misdemeanor, in Publishing the following Seditious Libels, viz. one call'd Cuto's another, Almost Gracious Speech paraphras'd in plain English Metre for the Use of the Vulgar; and a third, Pasquin to the Queen's Statue on St. Paul's: In which were several Seditious Verses and Expressions, highly reflecting on the King and Government
            </rs>. The Prisoner, it seems, was a private Hawker, and carried these, and other Things of the same Criminal Nature, about in his Budget; which being made known to a Person in Authority, he demanded his Budget in <placeName id="t17160712-3-crimeloc16">Westminster's-Hall</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17160712-3-crimeloc16" type="placeName" value="Westminster's-Hall"></interp>
